label.value: Classic Hodgkin Lymphoma Post-Transplant Lymphoproliferative Disorder

value.value: A lymphoproliferative disorder that fulfills the criteria for classic Hodgkin lymphoma and arises as a result of post-transplant immunosuppression therapy. It is most often seen in renal transplant patients.
A Burkitt lymphoma that arises in a patient with a history of organ transplantation.
A Burkitt-like lymphoma that arises in a patient with a history of organ transplantation.

label.value: Diffuse Large B-Cell Lymphoma Post-Transplant Lymphoproliferative Disorder

value.value: A diffuse large B-cell lymphoma that arises in a patient with a history of organ transplantation.
An anaplastic lymphoma that arises in a patient with a history of organ transplantation.
